    <thetext>BETA_JAVA8:

The following triggers two errors. I believe it should be accepted:

// ---------
interface I {
	Integer foo(X x);
}

public class X {

	int foo(I ...i) { return 10;}

	int goo() { return 0;}
	
	{
		foo(X::goo);
		foo(()-&gt; {return 10;});
	}
}

// ----------
Interestingly javac accepts the first call to foo and rejects the second.</thetext>
